Class PickerAgent.GetRobotAgents

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Enclosing class:
    PickerAgent

    private class PickerAgent.GetRobotAgents
extends jade.core.behaviours.SimpleBehaviour
    Behavior which is executed cyclicly every specified amount of time given by the argument period. The pickerAgent will query for robotAgents which are registered to the DF, description facilitator, and are offering the service of "fetch". Then, it will choose the robot nearest to the shelf, and send to it the coordinates of the target.

    • Method Detail

      • action

        public void action()
        Main action of the behavior. It implements the following thread of actions:
      • Search for RobotAgents which offer the service "fetch". Such robots are said to be free.
      • Once the IDs of the robots are extracted, it compares the position of the agents w.r.t. the target shelf.
      • The nearest robot wins, and the coordinates of the target is set to it.
